1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,060
 We just had this beautiful candles lit,

2
00:00:03,060 --> 00:00:07,000
 they're so nice, and we had the scripture read to us

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,460
 that says, "I am the vine,

4
00:00:10,460 --> 00:00:15,120
 "and you are the branches."

5
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:17,480
 These words just happen to be on our walls,

6
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,840
 and if you're wondering, you know,

7
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:21,720
 why are we choosing these words, you know,

8
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:22,720
 to put them on the wall?

9
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:26,040
 Is it for the purpose of decoration,

10
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:29,040
 or we needed something to be on the wall

11
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,160
 when we move into the building

12
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:32,400
 since we don't have any cross, or, you know.

13
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,840
 These are actually the very verse

14
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:37,720
 that shaped the identity of this church.

15
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:41,860
 We're a divine church, and if you are wondering,

16
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:43,200
 the name of the church, Divine,

17
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:46,880
 actually comes from these verse in John chapter 15.

18
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:51,400
 Indeed, if you've been around the last couple of weeks,

19
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:54,120
 we've been going on with this Advent series,

20
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:55,680
 we've been lighting the candle every week,

21
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:59,000
 we've been reading part of the scripture

22
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,320
 from the book of John in particular every single week.

23
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:05,240
 In the book of John, there were in total

24
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:08,280
 seven of these I am statements

25
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:11,480
 that Jesus declared while he was walking on the earth,

26
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,440
 and John recorded them, wrote them in his gospel.

27
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:18,720
 It was quite unique to the writings of his gospel.

28
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:22,720
 And there's a very important,

29
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:25,840
 there's a significance to these declaration

30
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:29,600
 that Jesus made, that John has recorded,

31
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,800
 because all these statements,

32
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:35,320
 they start with this phrase, I am.

33
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:38,360
 And that actually ties all the way back

34
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:43,020
 to the Old Testament, particularly to the book of Exodus.

35
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:45,160
 When Moses met God in that burning bush,

36
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:47,400
 sorry, don't burn, okay, yes.

37
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,800
 When God met Moses in that burning bush,

38
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,400
 he was asking God, like, what's your name

39
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,880
 if I have to introduce you,

40
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,520
 if I need to be, you know, your manager,

41
00:01:55,520 --> 00:01:59,600
 I gotta introduce you to those people, what do I say?

42
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,920
 And God gave him like this phrase,

43
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:07,220
 which in English we translate it as I am who I am,

44
00:02:07,220 --> 00:02:11,600
 or we call him Yahweh, which means he is who he is.

45
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:14,680
 And so whenever the Israelites,

46
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:18,800
 they were trying to refer to their God, the creator God,

47
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,800
 they don't even speak of this name,

48
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,680
 but they write of this name Yahweh,

49
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:25,480
 which means, yeah, I am who I am, or he is who he is.

50
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,360
 So he's the great I am,

51
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,440
 just like the song we sung moments ago.

52
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:34,920
 When Jesus made these claims, I am the bread of life,

53
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:38,280
 I am the light of the world, I am a good shepherd,

54
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:43,160
 he is basically referring to himself as God.

55
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:45,300
 And so that actually stir up some,

56
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:51,060
 well, different kinds of emotions or feelings in people.

57
00:02:51,060 --> 00:02:54,840
 To some, of course, they receive it gladly and think,

58
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:58,240
 yes, this is the son of God that I'm going to follow,

59
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:02,320
 he is the Messiah, I'm going to follow Jesus like 100%.

60
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:03,980
 But on the other hand, there are people,

61
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:07,480
 they were super offended, like, who are you to say that?

62
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,620
 Like, how could you say that?

63
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:13,960
 How could you claim to be God or the son of God?

64
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,360
 And they were furious.

65
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:18,160
 So people were pushed to a place

66
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,280
 where they have to make a decision.

67
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,200
 Is he who he says he is?

68
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:24,080
 And that's actually the same question

69
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:26,160
 that should be asked every Christmas,

70
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,680
 because Christmas, it's about this news,

71
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:32,500
 about this announcement that the savior of the world

72
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:37,200
 has come in a person, God has come in the person of Jesus.

73
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,880
 It forces us to be in a place

74
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:44,780
 to consider whether what he claimed is true.

75
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,360
 And what we couldn't do it,

76
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,920
 we couldn't just come and say,

77
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:50,220
 oh yeah, he gave some good advice, Jesus,

78
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:54,020
 this Jesus guy, he said this, he quote this,

79
00:03:54,020 --> 00:04:00,680
 giving it's even better than receiving.

80
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,680
 He has all these good moral teachings,

81
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,720
 so maybe I could just treat Jesus

82
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:08,000
 like those self-help books, like chicken soup.

83
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,680
 I can just take a few things from his teachings,

84
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:15,560
 but maybe he's a good teacher, he has good moral teachings.

85
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:18,280
 No, Christmas forces you to a place

86
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,360
 where you cannot remain there.

87
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,600
 You have to consider what he says about himself.

88
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:28,040
 He's either God or he is just a lunatic,

89
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,180
 or maybe he's a liar,

90
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:32,280
 and you gotta make a decision for yourself.

91
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,280
 Every Christmas, we're brought to this place

92
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:36,300
 like those people 2,000 years ago.

93
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,440
 We were brought to a place of decision.

94
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,040
 Who is Jesus?

95
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:44,160
 We have to make a decision for ourselves.

96
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:49,160
 When we encounter all these I am statements.

97
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:52,360
 Today we're going to look at another one of them.

98
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:56,560
 In John 15, just now, it was beautifully read.

99
00:04:56,560 --> 00:05:00,800
 Jesus, he declared, I am the true vine,

100
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,760
 and my father is the gardener.

101
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:08,200
 This first line in John 15,

102
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,360
 this line alone already,

103
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,280
 it's loaded with rich biblical history,

104
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,840
 and a rich message here.

105
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,880
 You see, in the Old Testament,

106
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:23,800
 there is a nation that was referred to as the vine,

107
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:27,680
 and that is Israel, the people of God.

108
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:31,280
 Or more accurately, the vine had been the symbol

109
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:34,380
 of Israel for centuries.

110
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:37,240
 It's kind of like the national emblem.

111
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:41,760
 And in fact, in the days of Jesus, at the temple,

112
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:46,760
 there is this great, magnificent, golden grapes

113
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:50,440
 like hanging as a part of the declaration

114
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,360
 at the entrance of the temple.

115
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,760
 They are so proud of it.

116
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:56,400
 When they look back, when they think about their identity

117
00:05:56,400 --> 00:06:00,240
 or this biblical symbol as grapes,

118
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:04,440
 they were so proud because that speaks of God's blessing

119
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:08,240
 and mission for this group of people.

120
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,960
 We know that the history of Israel

121
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,360
 goes all the way back to this guy named Abraham.

122
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,040
 And God said to Abraham,

123
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:17,520
 "I'm gonna make you and your family a big nation,

124
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:21,640
 and I'm going to bless you so that you would be a blessing,

125
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:24,880
 or you and your family would be a blessing

126
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,560
 to all the nations, all the families,

127
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,320
 all the people on the planet."

128
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:35,440
 This is somewhat captured in Isaiah 27, verse six.

129
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:40,320
 It says that, "In days to come, Jacob will take root.

130
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:42,880
 Israel will bud and blossom

131
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:46,920
 and fill all the world with fruit."

132
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:51,920
 The idea of Israel being divine is that it will bear fruit,

133
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:55,960
 that all the spiritual, all the blessings from God,

134
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:59,200
 it will become, they will be like vine

135
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,320
 and they will bear fruit like grapes.

136
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:04,560
 And all these fruits will bless the rest of the world.

137
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,840
 That has always been part of God's plan,

138
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:10,240
 but we know it didn't go that smoothly.

139
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:12,160
 We know that this nation, this people,

140
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:15,320
 they were corrupted by sin and selfishness.

141
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:18,400
 And so in the Bible, if we continue to read on,

142
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:21,800
 what we see is that in Isaiah, for example,

143
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:25,680
 Isaiah chapter five, it's called a song of the vineyard.

144
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:29,080
 And God described himself as a loving farmer

145
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:32,840
 who cleared the stones and planted the choices vine,

146
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:36,720
 and which was figuratively Israel.

147
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,880
 And he looked for the sweet grapes

148
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:41,000
 of justice and righteousness.

149
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,440
 So when we talk about fruits,

150
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,600
 we're talking about all the great things

151
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,560
 that a nation can experience or all they can do,

152
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:51,440
 like righteousness, goodness, kindness, and justice,

153
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:56,440
 all these that would build a harmonious society

154
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:58,040
 that is just and right,

155
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:01,160
 and people can live in God's blessing.

156
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:03,280
 That was God's plan for Israel,

157
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:06,000
 and through them a blessing to the nations.

158
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,320
 But no, we see that that was not the picture.

159
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:14,720
 Instead, the vine, you know, instead this vine in the Bible,

160
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:18,640
 in the Old Testament Israel, it produced wild grapes.

161
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:20,640
 It's sour, it's stinking.

162
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:24,480
 And we saw that in the stories of the Bible,

163
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,880
 the people of Israel, they were corrupted.

164
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:31,880
 And so in Psalm 80, and also in Jeremiah 2,

165
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:35,160
 we see that what was described as Israel

166
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:38,080
 was how they would turn to become a wild

167
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,440
 and degenerate a plant of vine.

168
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,800
 They had religion.

169
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:44,840
 Don't get me wrong, they still have their temple.

170
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:48,000
 They still have all these religious rituals and ceremonies,

171
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:52,320
 and they have all these things going on,

172
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,120
 religious activities going on,

173
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:58,200
 but they do not have fruit in them.

174
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:03,200
 It's like dead vine, it's wild vine, it's degenerate vine.

175
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:09,040
 It's nothing near what God has planned in the first place.

176
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:13,120
 And because this original vine had failed,

177
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:17,720
 God removed his protection, and the vineyard was trampled.

178
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:21,360
 Well, which refers to the event of exile

179
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,120
 in the history of Israel.

180
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:27,520
 That was the backdrop to this verse.

181
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,520
 Oh, sorry, not this verse,

182
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:33,520
 but to chapter 15 of the Gospel of John.

183
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:36,800
 When Jesus was saying these words,

184
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:41,600
 Jesus was, if you're following the passage in John 13,

185
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,240
 he was washing the disciples' feet

186
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:46,120
 after the last supper in this upper room.

187
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:50,160
 And then he gave a speech at chapter 14,

188
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:52,480
 and by the end of chapter 14, Jesus would say,

189
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,600
 hey, come on, let's go.

190
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:58,600
 And they were headed towards the Mount of Olives.

191
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,520
 And perhaps when they were passing

192
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,840
 through the Mount of Olives,

193
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,440
 biblical scholars, they were, you know, try to guess,

194
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:08,400
 maybe they walked through, walked past the temple,

195
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,280
 and Jesus saw the temple,

196
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:13,960
 and those hanging golden, magnificent,

197
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,520
 gigantic grapes on the temple.

198
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,120
 And he said these words, he said,

199
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:22,560
 I am the true vine, and my father is the gardener.

200
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:26,880
 I am the true vine, which means he's the real version.

201
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,360
 He's the genuine version.

202
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,080
 He's the original version.

203
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:32,120
 He is the original vine.

204
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:35,680
 He's what God has originally designed and planned

205
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:39,400
 for this entire humanity, all his creation,

206
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,760
 to experience the blessings of God.

207
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,440
 He is the true vine.

208
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:47,640
 So Jesus is saying, Israel was just a shadow.

209
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,560
 I am the substance.

210
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:52,040
 Israel was just a type, if you will,

211
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,800
 and I am the reality.

212
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:57,280
 I am that reality that Israel, as a type,

213
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,080
 was pointing towards.

214
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:03,080
 If Israel was called, like, the vine in the Old Testament,

215
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:06,240
 it was because Israel was a representative.

216
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:09,200
 It was pointing towards the true vine.

217
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,320
 That is me, Jesus says.

218
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:15,440
 This completely redraws the map of people of God.

219
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,440
 You know, in the old way, to be the people of God,

220
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,120
 you have to be Jewish by blood.

221
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:21,440
 You have to observe the Torah,

222
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:24,800
 which is the Old Testament law,

223
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,600
 but in the new way, now you belong to God.

224
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,880
 You're a part of God's people,

225
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:33,880
 simply by having this genuine connection with Jesus.

226
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:37,960
 And Jesus continues to describe the father's role

227
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,000
 as the gardener.

228
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,760
 He continued to say this, said,

229
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:45,040
 "He, the gardener, cuts off every branch in me

230
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,080
 "that bears no fruit.

231
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,000
 "While every branch that does bear fruit,

232
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:53,120
 "he prunes so that it will be even more fruitful.

233
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,040
 "You are already clean

234
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:59,160
 "because of the word I have spoken to you."

235
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:02,600
 The father is not a distant observer,

236
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,240
 but he is the vine dresser.

237
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,240
 He's the gardener.

238
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,760
 He's the one who is hands-on.

239
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:12,360
 He's the constantly working vine dresser.

240
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:16,320
 So he has, he would probably divide his work

241
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:19,000
 into two different categories.

242
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,200
 He's either cutting off branches

243
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,560
 or he's pruning these branches.

244
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,880
 We know that branches that don't bear fruit,

245
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:31,600
 that we see no fruit, no life in it.

246
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,240
 It's not producing anything.

247
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,800
 This gardener God, the father,

248
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,920
 would cut them off from the tree

249
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:41,480
 because normally branches that do not bear fruit

250
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,520
 means there's something wrong with it.

251
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,840
 Maybe there are bugs in it.

252
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:48,840
 Maybe it has some disease in it.

253
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,080
 If you don't cut it off,

254
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,080
 it will infect the rest of the plant.

255
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,920
 So it must be cut off.

256
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,880
 You cannot let it stay.

257
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,800
 Branches that don't bear fruit,

258
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,160
 meaning there is no life.

259
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:02,320
 You don't see the life of Jesus in these people.

260
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,800
 They said they come to church.

261
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,520
 They said they're part of the community,

262
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:09,160
 but you never really see the life of Jesus,

263
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,720
 the character of Jesus.

264
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,840
 You don't see any of that in them.

265
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,640
 They're just here.

266
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:19,840
 And in that group who are with Jesus,

267
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:23,280
 back then there is a guy whose name is Judas.

268
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,680
 He was part of the group,

269
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:27,840
 but he was never truly one of them.

270
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:32,440
 And then Jesus continues to say,

271
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:35,040
 but yeah, my father also does something else.

272
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:37,600
 He would come and prune.

273
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,600
 He will come and cut back a little bit

274
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,360
 from those branches.

275
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,200
 What branches?

276
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,360
 Those branches that could bear fruit

277
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:48,760
 or those branches that are bearing fruits.

278
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:55,120
 And this pruning process is never something

279
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:57,200
 that we consider comfortable.

280
00:13:57,200 --> 00:14:01,640
 But I just want to draw attention to this today.

281
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:05,600
 Maybe there are times you feel life, it's quite difficult

282
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,160
 after you have become a Christian,

283
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:10,040
 after you give your life to Jesus,

284
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:13,080
 after you have done everything that he asked you to.

285
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:15,520
 And you're wondering why life is so difficult.

286
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:19,600
 Why I'm still having this conflict with my spouse,

287
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,720
 with my colleagues.

288
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:23,720
 Why am I still going through this difficulty in life?

289
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:25,720
 Why am I going through all that?

290
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:29,640
 I just want to draw attention here today

291
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:33,680
 to the fact that God doesn't prune those branches

292
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,960
 that are not bearing fruit.

293
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:39,960
 He prunes those branches that are foot bearing,

294
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:45,040
 which means before he comes and does something in your life

295
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,600
 and say, "Oh, I got to cut off something.

296
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,000
 I need to let you go through some challenges."

297
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:52,400
 Before he does that, first he saw something in us.

298
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:56,240
 He saw that we are indeed bearing fruits.

299
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:59,320
 That's why a lot of the stories I heard,

300
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:02,520
 why challenges always comes when you start to follow God,

301
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,520
 when you start to give your life to God,

302
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:07,760
 when you start to see something in your life

303
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,720
 and then those challenges come.

304
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,880
 God is saying, "Hey, there are things in your life

305
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:15,360
 that will suck the life out,

306
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:19,600
 that is not allowing you to bear fruit.

307
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,400
 Maybe there are distractions in your life.

308
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:24,240
 Maybe there are things that does not align

309
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:26,080
 with the life I want to give you.

310
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:29,080
 So I have to take away some of those things.

311
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,960
 I need to ask you to lay down some of those things.

312
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,720
 I need you to go through these challenges

313
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,760
 so you can continue to grow."

314
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:37,720
 And that's never easy.

315
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,320
 That's never comfortable.

316
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:43,480
 But if God has never seen those fruits in your life,

317
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,160
 He would never have done that.

318
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:51,680
 So today, or maybe in the past,

319
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,480
 or maybe in the future,

320
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:57,880
 if you ever see yourself going through some hardships

321
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:01,440
 in life, some challenges, some real difficulties,

322
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:05,760
 can I suggest that it's the loving act of the Father,

323
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:10,760
 the gardener who is helping us to bear more fruit?

324
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:13,560
 And that's what Jesus is suggesting here.

325
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:16,040
 Say, "Yeah, I know sometimes life can be hard

326
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,360
 when the Father comes and prunes us."

327
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:20,760
 Because there are places,

328
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:21,920
 there are some things in our life

329
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,640
 that were reflecting Jesus,

330
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,120
 but there are some things that

331
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:29,200
 that are not reflecting Jesus in our lives.

332
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,240
 And He wants to take that away.

333
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:34,240
 He wants us to bear fruits.

334
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:40,240
 And so here Jesus, He continues to say in verse four,

335
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:45,320
 says, "Remain in me, and I also remain in you.

336
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:47,480
 No branch can bear fruit by itself.

337
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,480
 It must remain in the vine.

338
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:53,400
 Neither can you bear fruit unless you remain in me.

339
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:56,480
 I am the vine, you are the branches.

340
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:58,520
 If you remain in me and I in you,

341
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:00,320
 you will bear much fruit.

342
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,640
 Apart from me, you can do nothing.

343
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:04,360
 If you do not remain in me,

344
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:08,160
 you are like a branch that is thrown away and withers.

345
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,160
 Such branches are picked up,

346
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,760
 thrown into the fire and burn.

347
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:17,120
 If you remain in me and my words remain in you,

348
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:21,120
 ask whatever you wish, and it will be done for you.

349
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:25,320
 This is to my Father's glory that you bear much fruit,

350
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:28,840
 showing yourselves to be my disciples."

351
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:34,360
 So interesting what Jesus is describing here

352
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:37,440
 between the relationships of Him as the vine

353
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:41,800
 and us as the branches was part of this vine.

354
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,600
 He said, you know, we cannot do anything apart from Him.

355
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:48,720
 We cannot have that power of life.

356
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:49,800
 We don't have that.

357
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:53,040
 We don't have the source of joy, source of love.

358
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:56,400
 We don't have any of that if we're not in Him.

359
00:17:56,400 --> 00:18:00,120
 But so as the branches, we are drawing our life,

360
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:03,880
 we're drawing our joy and peace and love.

361
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,000
 We're drawing all these qualities,

362
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,400
 all these life qualities from the vine itself.

363
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,000
 But then at the same time,

364
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:16,000
 the vine Jesus is bearing fruit in this world

365
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,480
 through His branches.

366
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:22,600
 That plan that God always has for the vine to grow

367
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,160
 and bear fruit and bless the entire world,

368
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:29,760
 you know, for the descendants of Abraham

369
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:32,080
 to be blessed so that they will be a blessing.

370
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:36,960
 This whole idea, the idea of fruit bearing

371
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:39,040
 to bless the rest of the world,

372
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:45,520
 Jesus says, "It's my branches bearing these fruits

373
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,960
 that will bless the world."

374
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,120
 Let me say this again, as branches,

375
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:52,800
 we are to draw life from Jesus.

376
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:55,000
 He's the source of our life.

377
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,640
 But then the vine says,

378
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,960
 "I'm going to bear fruit and bless this world."

379
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:00,800
 Through whom?

380
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:04,120
 Through the branches that is connected in me.

381
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:10,280
 We are part of that plan for God to bless this world.

382
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:13,760
 He said, "I'm doing this through this vine.

383
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:16,440
 I'm doing this through the branches of the vine."

384
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:18,960
 It will be the fruits hanging on these branches.

385
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:21,480
 It will be the life, it will be the power,

386
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:24,240
 it will be the love, the joy that is displayed

387
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:28,680
 in all these branches that are sitting here right now.

388
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,920
 When they're in the world around them,

389
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:33,520
 when they're in this community, this neighborhood,

390
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:36,280
 it will be the fruits in your life,

391
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,840
 in my life, in our lives,

392
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:41,200
 that will become a blessing to the world around us.

393
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:44,040
 But we will never be able to bear fruit

394
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:47,920
 if we're not connected to the source.

395
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,520
 That is Jesus.

396
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:53,400
 And so he says, "Remain in me."

397
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:56,480
 This is quite interesting.

398
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:59,280
 The word remain in itself,

399
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:03,840
 it suggests or it carries a sense of continuity

400
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,240
 in terms of time.

401
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:08,000
 Like when you have to remain in a place,

402
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,600
 it means it takes a while.

403
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,920
 There should be a stretch of time.

404
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,880
 You can't just go there, "Oh, I've arrived, I'm leaving."

405
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:19,360
 If you have to remain in the place, it takes time.

406
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:22,360
 And the other thing is that, you know,

407
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,080
 when it talks about biblical commands,

408
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:25,920
 especially in the New Testament,

409
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:30,920
 let's say when Paul wrote in Ephesians 5, verse 18,

410
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,840
 if you've been to an alpha,

411
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,240
 you probably have heard about this.

412
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,640
 He says, Paul says,

413
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:38,160
 "You have to be filled with the Holy Spirit."

414
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,120
 If we look at the original language, Greek,

415
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,600
 we look at the grammar, the tense,

416
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:46,200
 that the biblical author Paul was using.

417
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,560
 It was in Greek, it's called present tense,

418
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:51,240
 but what it means is actually our English

419
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,280
 present continuous tense,

420
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:56,120
 which means normally when we translate that verse,

421
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:58,120
 we're saying, "Be filled with the Holy Spirit."

422
00:20:58,120 --> 00:21:02,640
 It means you have to keep being filled with the Holy Spirit.

423
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:07,320
 It has to be an ongoing, it's a present continuous motion.

424
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,640
 You have to come back to this again and again.

425
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:12,120
 It has to keep happening in our lives.

426
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:14,760
 Earlier this year, at the beginning of this year,

427
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:18,520
 my first sermon this year was on 1 Thessalonians

428
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:22,400
 that says, "Rejoice always, pray without ceasing,

429
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,080
 "give thanks in all circumstances."

430
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:26,500
 It was written in this present tense

431
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,680
 or our present continuous tense.

432
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:33,440
 You have to keep rejoicing, you have to keep praying,

433
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:37,640
 you have to keep giving thanks again and again.

434
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,640
 When Jesus says, "You have to seek first

435
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,600
 "the kingdom of God,"

436
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,720
 he's saying this in the present tense,

437
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,760
 but when you expect him to say, "Remain in me,"

438
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,200
 you expect that to be in this present

439
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:53,360
 or present continuous tense, "Keep remaining in me,"

440
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:55,040
 that's what we would have guessed

441
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:57,400
 what he's saying here or what would be written here

442
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:01,040
 grammatically, John actually wrote something else.

443
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:05,400
 He actually used a different tense in Greek to write this,

444
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:09,480
 a tense that basically describes that action of remaining

445
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:13,840
 as a complete decisive action in itself.

446
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,520
 So I know this is super abstract,

447
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:18,840
 but if you think about photos, videos,

448
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,320
 if you think normally the commands

449
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:23,280
 would be like filming a video, it's an ongoing thing,

450
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:26,840
 this is a snapshot, this is just one snapshot.

451
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:29,160
 This is just one moment that looking at

452
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:31,320
 what Jesus is saying here,

453
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:33,560
 it's not wake up every morning

454
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:37,640
 and anxiously try to reestablish your connection with me.

455
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,920
 He's not saying that.

456
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:42,680
 Instead, when John recorded this in the tense

457
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:46,280
 that kind of like a one off, like a one complete action

458
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:50,720
 when he say this, he is basically referring to this.

459
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:53,840
 Jesus is saying, "Take up your residence in me.

460
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:56,600
 "Settle this issue once and for all.

461
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,000
 "Do this, just move for good."

462
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,040
 It's like people who move to another country,

463
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:05,520
 you move for good, remain in me, come and settle in me,

464
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:09,520
 settle for good from now on, just stay in me,

465
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:10,960
 just remain here.

466
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:15,400
 In other words, Jesus is asking us to make a decision

467
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,800
 when he said that to his disciples.

468
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,440
 He's saying that you have to make a decision

469
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:25,160
 to live in me for good, for the rest of your life.

470
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:29,320
 You have to make that decision today.

471
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:32,000
 You have to make a decision for yourself.

472
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,040
 Just like at the beginning of this message,

473
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:36,600
 I said Christmas is a time that pushes us

474
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:38,080
 towards a decision.

475
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:40,520
 Who do we consider Jesus to be?

476
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:43,040
 We have to make a decision for ourselves.

477
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:46,840
 Here, Jesus is asking those who follow him

478
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,560
 to say, "You remain in me,

479
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:51,120
 "but you gotta make a decision right now."

480
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:53,680
 It's a once and for all decision.

481
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:58,920
 And we know that when this word for remain

482
00:23:58,920 --> 00:24:02,560
 in the original tense in Greek,

483
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:05,160
 it emphasized that kind of residence remaining,

484
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:08,400
 but it's not just, it shouldn't be translated

485
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,760
 as you should remain with me.

486
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:13,360
 It's not just about proximity.

487
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:15,400
 Jesus is saying remain in me.

488
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:18,240
 This translation means it's the position

489
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:20,720
 or the location, where are you?

490
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:25,600
 Us remaining in Jesus, it's like,

491
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,880
 we're not just me coming near to pass it to him,

492
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,280
 staying with him, hang with him, hang out with him

493
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,160
 like he's my buddy or he's my buddy,

494
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:36,000
 but it's not just about hanging out with him.

495
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,960
 When Jesus asked him to remain in him,

496
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:41,120
 it's like fish belongs in water,

497
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,560
 birds would fly in the air,

498
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:46,640
 that kind of remain in that environment.

499
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:49,080
 He says, Jesus says, "I am the environment

500
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:51,600
 "that you should be in."

501
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:55,720
 Oh, like, I'm sure the disciples have no clue

502
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,320
 what he was talking about.

503
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,240
 But if we continue to read on

504
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:02,160
 what does it mean remain in Jesus?

505
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:05,560
 Biblical scholars, when they look at

506
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:08,040
 John chapter 15, they would say,

507
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:10,560
 verse one to eight is the parable

508
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:12,880
 of the vine and branches,

509
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:16,760
 but nine to 16, it's actually the explanation

510
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:21,200
 of this, like a metaphor, if you will.

511
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:24,400
 So chapter 15, verse nine says this,

512
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:28,040
 "As the Father has loved me, so have I loved you.

513
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:31,560
 "Now remain in my love."

514
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:34,640
 If you keep my commands, you will remain in my love,

515
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,000
 just as I have kept my Father's commands

516
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:39,520
 and remain in his love.

517
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:42,600
 When Jesus says remain in me,

518
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:46,400
 when we put these two paragraphs side by side,

519
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,680
 what he was meaning is remain in me

520
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:50,840
 means remain in my love,

521
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,760
 and what is the love of Jesus?

522
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:56,400
 These words were spoken like maybe 12, 14 hours

523
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,640
 right before he was nailed on that cross.

524
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,840
 He says, let me show you what I mean

